<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-20T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-20T10:00:00-05:00" n="550" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d550">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.91262/199: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-20T17:00:00+02:00">March 20,
                                    1941—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 6:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1039. Hottelet visited today by Embassy representative who found him
                            obviously well and composed and without complaint as to conditions and
                            treatment. He wished his family and home office assured of his
                            confidence that his case will be settled soon and satisfactorily and he
                            sends best greetings. Arrangements made to provide him with reading
                            matter and desired personal items. Hottelet was reassured that Embassy
                            is following case closely. Local United Press office informed of
                            visit.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>